AccuracyFormBlock.minimumDocFreqDescript: Установите минимальную частоту сохраненных логов в ElasticSearch (Индекс), в которых должно употребляться слово из анализируемого лога. Если количество логов ниже указанного значения, данное слово будет игнорироваться в Авто-Анализе. Чем чаще оно употребляется в Индексе, тем меньше значения оказывает на результаты Авто-Анализа.
AccuracyFormBlock.minimumShouldMatchDesc: Процент совпадения слов между анализируемым логом и логом, сохраненным в ElasticSearch. Логи из ElasticSearch c процентом ниже установленного будут игнорировать в Авто-Анализе.
AccuracyFormBlock.minimumTermFreqDescrip: Установите минимальную частоту слова в анализируемом логе. Если количество слов ниже указанного значения, это слово будет игнорироваться в Авто-Анализе. Чем чаще оно употребляется в анализируемом логе, тем больше значение оказывает на результаты Авто-Анализа.
AccuracyFormBlock.numberOfLogLinesDescri: Количество первых строк лога, которые будут учитываться при Авто-Анализе.

WidgetTypeSelector.heading: Choose widget type from the list below
Widgets.Description.activity_stream: Shows all activities occurring on the project.
Widgets.Description.bug_trend: Shows the trend of growth in the number of failed test cases from run to run.
Widgets.Description.cases_trend:
- in "Launch Mode" shows the increment of test-cases from run to run,
- in "Timeline Mode" shows the increment of test-cases distributed by dates (in launches with the largest number of test-cases per day).
Widgets.Description.cumulative: Shows the growth trend of summary statistics of launches with the same tag prefix.
Widgets.Description.flaky_test_cases: Shows the TOP-20 the most flaky test cases within the specified previous launches.
Widgets.Description.investigated_trend:
- in "Launch Mode" shows whether the launches are analyzed or not (the percentage of "Investigated"/"To Investigate") from run to run,
- in "Timeline Mode" shows percentage of "Investigated"/"To Investigate" tests in all runs per day distributed by dates.
Widgets.Description.launch_statistics: Shows statistics of the last launch divided into 2 sections:</br> - Skipped, Passed, Failed </br> - Product Bug, System Issue, To Investigate, Automation Bugs.
Widgets.Description.launches_comparison_: Allows to compare statistics for 2 last launches side by side.
Widgets.Description.launches_duration_ch: Shows duration of the selected launches.
Widgets.Description.launches_table: Shows the configurable table of launches.
Widgets.Description.most_failed_test_cas: Shows the TOP-20 most failing test cases within the specified previous launches.
Widgets.Description.not_passed: Shows the percent ratio of non-passed test cases (Failed + Skipped) to Total cases from run to run.
Widgets.Description.overall_statistics: Shows summary of test cases with each statuses in the selected launches.
Widgets.Description.passing_rate_per_lau: Shows the percentage ratio of Passed test cases to Total cases for last run of selected launch.
Widgets.Description.passing_rate_summary: Shows the percentage ratio of Passed test cases to Total cases for set of launches.
Widgets.Description.product_status: Shows the configurable table that is representing launch statistics or group statistics by special filter.
Widgets.Description.statistic_trend:
- in "Launch mode" shows the growth trend in the number of test cases with each selected statuses from run to run,
- in "Timeline mode" shows sum, distributed by dates.
Widgets.Description.unique_bug_table: Shows real identified bugs, posted to the Bug Tracking System, and existing in the BTS bugs, loaded on the project.
